              <additions>
                <p/>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="addition1">
                     <p>Other lessons have been noted on the margins, throughout the volume, by a later hand.</p>
                  </item>
                   <item n="2" xml:id="addition2">
                      <locus from="8" to="8"/>
                      <p>Fol. 8 is a comparatively modern <material>paper</material> leaf. </p>
                   </item>
                   <item n="3" xml:id="addition3">
                      <locus from="68a" to="68a"/>
                      <p>At the foot of fol. 68a, after the doxology, stand the words</p>
                      <p><quote xml:lang="syr">ܢܘܢܐ ܟܬ݁[ܒܬ]</quote>,</p>
                      <p><quote>“I <persName ref="">Nonnus</persName>, have written,"</quote></p>
                      <p>separated by an ornament.</p>
                   </item>
                   <item n="4" xml:id="addition4">
                      <locus from="106" to="106"/>
                      <p>The last page has been entirely rewritten by a modern hand, which has also retouched several other pages.</p>
                   </item>
